{
  "text": "Mitochondrial ultrastructure was evaluated using transmission EM to support data from ECHO and mtDNA abundance using methods that resemble those used regularly in the laboratory. [CITATION_1] Each EM photograph was reviewed independently by two investigators for the presence of structurally abnormal mitochondria, increased numbers of mitochondrial profiles per field, intramitochondrial lamellar bodies, abnormal cristae density, cristae reduplication, mitochondrial swelling, and intramitochondrial paracrystals as performed by others. [CITATION_2] Histological Analysis Heart samples were processed, sectioned (6 mm), stained with hematoxylin and eosin (H&E), and examined microscopically as done by us earlier. [CITATION_3] Images were stored electronically to compare histopathological features.",
  "correct_citation": {
